OS_Byte 129  Get buffer/mouse status
#Parent OS_ByteIndex
=>	R0 =	129 (&81)
		R1,R2	vary depending upon operation
#line;tab
This call provides four distinct operations, distinguished by the values in *both* R1 and R2. These operations are:
#wrap off
{f24}g{f}	<To read a key within a time limit=>OS_Byte129a>
{f24}g{f}	<To read the OS version identifier=>OS_Byte129b>
{f24}g{f}	<To scan the keyboard for a range of keys=>OS_Byte129c>
{f24}g{f}	<To scan the keyboard for a single key=>OS_Byte129d>
#wrap
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 870=>PRM-1:870>
